detailedDescription.articleBody:
Kallum Michael Higginbotham is an English footballer who plays for Dunfermline Athletic, as a winger. He can also play as a striker.
Higginbotham started his football career as a youth player at Salford City and then in Oldham Athletic's reserve squad. Having failed to break into the first team at Boundary Park, Higginbotham joined League One side Rochdale in 2007. He was later loaned to Accrington Stanley, having fallen out of favour. He joined Scottish First Division side Falkirk in June 2010, where he enjoyed two successful seasons with the club.
